eds encrypt and distribute the information across numerous immutable distributed ledgers. The technology distributes the data across different chains in the form of puzzle pieces.<br>It then rebuilds the data once secure authentication using a multi-signature logic has been completed.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"what-makes-this-technology-from-verv-so-unique\"><\/span>What Makes this Technology from Verv So Unique?<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The system used by Verv has complied fully with data privacy and regulatory security standards of the US and the EU. Some of these standards include PCI-DSS, SCA, and GDPR. The features that make this technology so unique include:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Impossible to hack or attack with a malware<\/li><li>Customers will continue to own their private information at all times<\/li><li>Information never leaves the customer\u2019s private storage area<\/li><li>The client can give access to third parties if and when they want<\/li><li>At any one time, only one client having one device and one key can access the stored data.<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Verv provides a fully loaded, wide-ranging white-labelled solution for interested parties. It covers everything from virtual cards and physical cards to a branded mobile application. Clients can issue cards to their employees and use them to deposit and withdraw funds online.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>You can now accept over 250 payment methods with Verv, enabling your business to expand into new markets and territories. Read on to learn more about Verv!<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":875,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[17,16,14],"tags":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/874"}],"collection":[{"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":